aning, from discussions of neuroscience to computational social science. It provides both the definitive introduction to the sociological literature on culture as well as a critical set of case studies for methods courses across the social sciences.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aCulturexResearchxMethodology. 0aCulture. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh1 aBail, Christopher A., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aFrye, Margaret, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLizardo, Omar, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMcDonnell, Terence E., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMische, Ann, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aTavory, Iddo, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWherry, Frederick F., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311071097708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW40uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/mohr1802840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231542586423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231542586.jpg  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-071097-7  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-P